second anyone who has followed the results of the dialogue 
between the two sides up to now will easily realize that there is 
no positive result the us could not even obtain initial israeli 
approval of the baker plan which the plo had reservations over 
third american insistence on a plo condemnation of the raid 
provokes the issue of equal treatment and specifically a request 
from israel for a condemnation of the terrorist acts it practices 
against the palestiniaian people 
fourth just as the plo is asked to condemn an act it has not 
perpetrated so should israel be requested to condemn violent acts 
it has not perpetrated such as those against plo members in many 
countries 
the american threat to cut off the dialogue with the plo has no 
gravity neither as concerns the value of the dialogue nor as 
concerns the justice of the request especially after the formation 
of a government of war in israel 
