like that of human beings does not need to be justified 
the real question is to ask what would happen to canadians 
identity complex if the country were to disappear what would 
replace it what surer identity awaits the doubting canadian if 
there is none is it not better to look within the nation and 
examine the links which are there however problematic these might 
be rather than seek the sense of self either through divisiveness 
at home or distinctiveness abroad 
this sounds negative and necessarily so for ethnic identity in 
all multicultural societies is a negative starting point the whole 
point is to move beyond that line creating an identity in the very 
act of looking for one for countries again like children are not 
just born but grow 
