<TEXT>
nelson mandelas delayed 
arrival in the united states on wednesday for lack of rest was not 
surprising considering the grueling schedule he has kept since 
being released from prison 
the 71yearold african national congress leader is on his third 
international tour in four months between trips he has kept up a 
nonstop routine of meetings with colleagues and opponents in south 
africa and crisscrossed the country appearing at rallies in every 
major city 
before leaving june 4 on the current sixweek 14nation tour 
mandela spent a week in the hospital getting rest as well as a 
checkup during an extensive physical examination a cyst was 
discovered on his bladder and he underwent an operation seven days 
before boarding the plane 
as a former amateur heavyweight boxer mandela prides himself on 
being in exceptional physical condition for his age and he worked 
hard at staying in shape during the 27 years he spent jailed for 
his action against south africas government 
but many of those years were spent at hard labor with inadequate 
diet black prisoners were given one thin blanket and forced to 
wear short pants through much of the winter during mandelas first 
years at robben island prison 
i feel on top of the world mandela said at a june 2 
hospital news conference journalists however said he looked 
tired 
from the moment he stepped through the prison gates feb 11 
mandela has kept a schedule that leaves little time for rest 
after a motorcade from the prison to the center of cape town he 
waited hours to give his first speech from a balcony at city hall 
the next day he subjected himself to a lengthy international news 
conference and hours of meetings with anc organizers and leaders 
on feb 13 he flew to johannesburg and presented himself to 
more than 100000 people at a rally in soweto the black township 
outside johannesburg 
he wanted to go home to live in the tiny brick house he had 
rented in the township for 40 years but after weeks of constant 
attention from neighbors tourists and journalists peering over 
his back wall he moved into a hilltop mansion that his wife 
winnie built in 1987 
still mandela has seldom had time alone with his family he is 
constantly surrounded by bodyguards aides and anc officials 
from feb 14 to 23 mandela participated in allday meetings 
with journalists diplomats churchmen old friends and new 
antiapartheid officials he sat in his garden or his house and 
greeted visitors from morning until late at night for 10 days 
straight 
on feb 25 he flew halfway across south africa to address more 
than 100000 people in sweltering durban then returned to 
bloemfontein for an afternoon rally 
two days later he made his first international tour since 1962 
visiting exiled anc members and holding talks with leaders in five 
african countries and in sweden he was elected to his old post as 
deputy president of the anc and returned home with the added duties 
and expectations the title brought 
the nonstop interviews and briefings continued until march 12 
when the anc announced that meetings with mandela would be granted 
on a more selective basis 
he flew to namibia for the neighboring countrys independence 
celebrations on march 21 he apologized to the us and soviet 
foreign ministers for making them come to him to talk because his 
schedule was so tight 
back in south africa he attended rallies march 23 and 26 
visited hospitalized black marchers wounded by police march 28 and 
participated in two rallies at opposite ends of the country on 
march 29 and april 1 
after three more rallies in three cities mandela met with 
president fw de klerk in cape town on april 5 and then flew to 
lusaka zambia to consult with the anc national executive 
committee on april 8 
on april 11 he gave a news conference in johannesburg on april 
14 flew to london for a concert in his honor and on april 17 
attended zimbabwes independence celebrations he returned to 
johannesburg april 21 and the next day flew to his homeland 
transkei for visits with relatives and two more rallies 
from may 24 mandela led the african national congress in talks 
with the government in cape town during may he made another tour 
of african nations held three news conferences and three more 
rallies before entering the hospital 
</TEXT>
