<TEXT>
former east german leader erich honecker 
denied wednesday that his government harbored terrorists and blamed 
the charges on a campaign against the good reputation of his 
regime 
the 77yearold honecker in a rare public statement defended 
what he said was his communist governments pursuit of peace and 
battle against terrorism 
nothing in these accusations corresponds to reality 
honecker said in a statement released through the east german 
government news agency adn 
his denial came after authorities arrested nine reputed members 
of the notorious red army faction a leftist group blamed for a 
series of bombings and killings in west germany 
all the suspects had phony identities and some said they were 
aided by members of honeckers secret police some had been 
fugitives more than a decade 
all were arrested during a twoweek stretch beginning june 6 
after west german authorities and east germanys current democratic 
government launched a hunt for terrorist suspects 
honeckers comments were the latest entry in the furious debate 
over the terrorist ties of the old regime and the sinister 
espionage war between two nations about to unify 
western authorities have long alleged the east german government 
harbored supported and perhaps trained terrorists 
the west german newspaper die welt said wednesday that east 
germanys secret police knew in advance and tolerated a 1986 
bomb attack on a west german disco by libyan terrorists two us 
soldiers and a turkish woman were killed and 229 people were 
injured 
honecker defended his stalinist government which used the vast 
secret police network to maintain his ironfisted rule for nearly 
two decades until it was toppled in october during the peaceful 
anticommunist revolution 
with the current campaign apparently the good reputation of 
the german democratic republic as a stronghold of peace and the 
easing of tensions in the world is being undermined the 
statement said 
he said the campaign seeks to negate the peaceful relations 
between the german states that honecker said he championed 
east german interior minister petermichael diestel said monday 
that harboring west german terrorists was the personal hobby of 
honecker and his ousted security chief erich mielke 
the red army faction waged a deadly terrorist war against west 
german capitalism and nato in the 1970s and 1980s the most recent 
victim deutsche bank chief alfred herrhausen was killed in a 
bombing attack in november 
like every other citizen i have followed the arrests of the 
