<TEXT>
the ticker tape parade wednesday for nelson 
mandela is the fifth in the last 10 years through new yorks 
canyon of heroes on lower broadway 
there have been about twoscore such parades since charles 
lindbergh was lionized here in 1927 aviators athletes and 
warriors predominate 
among the notable parades 
1986 new york mets after beating the boston red sox in the 
world series 
1985 25000 vietnam veterans led by gen william westmoreland 
and 26 medal of honor winners in a 10yearslater welcomehome 
tribute 
1984 221 athletes of the us olympic team are cheered but 
101 spectators are injured when a construction scaffold on the 
parade route gives way 
1981 welcome home for the americans hostages freed from iran 
1979 pope john paul ii 
1978 new york yankees world champion team 
1969 miracle mets world champion team 
1969 astronauts neil armstrong and buzz aldrin the first men 
to land on the moon and fellow apollo 11 astronaut michael collins 
1963 astronaut gordon cooper 
1962 astronaut john glenn the first american in orbit 
1958 van cliburn the only classical musician ever to get the 
tickertape treatment after winning piano competition in moscow 
1951 gen douglas macarthur after his recall from korea by 
president truman 
1938 douglas wrongway corrigan for his air flight to 
ireland while claiming his destination was los angeles 
1938 howard hughes and his plane crew for breaking wiley 
posts roundtheworld flight record 
1936 beryl markham for the first westward transatlantic solo 
flight described later in her memoir west with the night 
1928 amelia earhart first woman to fly the atlantic as 
navigator before making her own solo flight some years later 
1927 lindbergh after returning from solo flight to paris 
several of the parades were larger in scope than the traditional 
route from bowling green to city hall a canyon about 16 blocks 
long formed by the office towers along broadway in the financial 
district 
glenns parade which wended through midtown as well as lower 
manhattan produced the greatest fallout of paper in any ticker 
tape parade 3474 tons according to sanitation department records 
the most paper generated by a canyononly parade was 1262 for 
the iran hostage parade 
official estimates of spectator numbers have been extravagant 
the mets 1986 parade was reported as drawing 22 million people 
that works out to 137000 people per block or enough to fill shea 
stadium 2 times 
