producing mostly hatching eggs will be eligible to vote 
in 1988 congress amended the egg research and consumer 
information act to suspend refunds for 18 months beginning jan 1 
1989 pending results of a national referendum 
for the new provision to be adopted approval would have to come 
from at least twothirds of those voting this summer or a majority 
of producers representing at least twothirds of the volume of eggs 
produced by all voters 
