<TEXT>
the food and drug administration on wednesday 
approved a new combination drug treatment that has been shown to 
prolong survival for patients with advanced stages of colon cancer 
the therapy combines levamisole a drug previously approved only 
for eliminating intestinal parasites in animals with fluorouracil 
already approved for treatment of several types of cancer 
fda officials said the combination of the two drugs in patients 
who have undergone surgery for colon cancer that has spread to 
nearby lymph nodes has been shown to reduce tumor reccurence and 
death in some patients 
michael friedman associate director of the cancer therapy 
evaluation program of the national cancer institute said the 
combination drug therapy is an important advance but he 
added studies on it must continue to improve treatment and 
determine whether it is effective for other stages of the disease 
colon cancer that has spread to lymph nodes is classified as 
stage 3 also referred to as stage dukes c about 21000 of the 
110000 americans diagnosed with colon cancer each year are in this 
stage about 40 percent live for five years or more after surgery 
the fda said 
the combination therapy was tested in two clinical trials 
sponsored by the national cancer institute that involved about 
1700 patients who had undergone surgery for stage 3 colon cancer 
researchers found that the treatment reduced the death rate for 
these patients by about onethird and the tumorrecurrence rate by 
about 40 percent 
they dont know however how the fiveyear survival rate will 
be affected since they have not followed these test patients that 
long yet said fda spokeswoman eva kemper 
more than 4000 patients with stage 3 colon cancer have received 
the combination therapy since may 1989 when it was approved under 
the fdas treatment ind investigative new drug program that makes 
promising experimental drugs available to patients with no other 
hope the agency said 
the most common side effects of the treatment are nausea 
occasional vomiting headache diarrhea sores in the mouth and 
depressed blood count the fda said also a blood disorder called 
agranulocytosis caused one death among patients in the cancer 
institute trials 
the therapy which lasts one year consists of levamisole 
tablets given orally for three consecutive days every other week 
and fluorouracil given intravenously once a week 
</TEXT>
