guerrilla offensive in san salvador in november negotiations in 
1984 and 1987 under late president jose napoleon duarte ended in 
deadlock 
the war has turned el salvador into the largest recipient of 
us aid in the western hemisphere the central american nation 
receives about 1 million a day from washington 
