<TEXT>
weeks of security planning and drills paid off 
wednesday as 750000 people welcomed nelson mandela to new york 
without incident police said 
we did a lot of planning put a lot of police officers on the 
street handpicked the ranking officers on the scene and it all 
came to fruition said assistant chief thomas walsh commander of 
patrol officers in southern manhattan 
things looked great it was terrific walsh added 
no arrests were reported during mandelas stops at a brooklyn 
high school or during the tickertape parade honoring the 
antiapartheid leader 
there was a point when the things got tense a bunch of youths 
in their exuberance rushed the mandelamobile but we had 70 
police officers on each side of the flatbed truck and they held 
them back the chief said 
nobody was arrested in the incident which took place as the 
bulletproof vehicle neared city hall the chief said 
officers also moved a small group of demonstrators to a spot 
near city hall but out of the march route 
everything went smoothly from the beginning of the day right 
through said police deputy commissioner of public information 
suzanne trazoff 
security for mandelas threeday visit to new york exceeded the 
protection provided for soviet president mikhail gorbachev and 
rivaled measures taken to protect pope john paul ii during his 
visit in 1979 
three thousand police officers were assigned to protect mandela 
on wednesday part of 12000 officers slated to protect the 
71yearold civil rights leader during his new york visit 
the elaborate security plans codenamed operation topaz took 
state department officials and police six weeks to develop and 
ranged from the development of the mandelamobile to deployment 
of 6200 sawhorses for crowd control 
operation topaz was also the largest safety effort ever mounted 
by the state departments office of diplomatic security which 
provides protection to dignitaries who arent heads of state said 
spokeswoman meg ravnholt 
one of the jewels of the security plan was the specially 
designed 58000 mandelamobile a flatbed truck with a 
bulletproof glass bubble that held mandela his wife winnie and 
four aides 
the specially outfitted vehicle included such james bond touches 
as an explosionproof fuel tank and tires filled with 
bulletresistant material said trazoff 
state department agents used electronic devices as well as 
bombsniffing labrador retrievers to sweep the stops on mandelas 
schedule during his public appearances police and federal agents 
formed a 75foot security zone around mandela to keep him at a safe 
distance from onlookers 
undercover police officers and detectives were among the crowds 
lining the parade route and rooftops along the way were guarded by 
uniformed sharpshooters said police sources who spoke on condition 
of anonymity 
