<TEXT>
about 80 aids activists were arrested 
wednesday on the opening day of an international conference on the 
deadly disease part of a coordinated effort to make their concerns 
known to the public 
the activists have created a polished organization for the sixth 
international conference on aids with banks of computers media 
advance people and a schedule of events complete with a theme for 
the day 
despite some earlier calls for riot and anarchy the aids 
coalition to unleash power known as act up and several other 
groups have joined together to coordinate an agenda of protest and 
politicking before the 12000 conference delegates and national 
media 
