don byers observed his 19th birthday 
in a foxhole 6 feet long 6 feet deep and about 2 feet wide and 
has the same plans for his 59th on feb 4 1991 
lt col byers is the last activeduty soldier from the korean 
war still serving on the peninsula 
the birthday foxhole on a hillside at chipyongni southeast of 
seoul is halffilled with earth after nearly 40 years and a small 
pine tree grows out of it 
byers said his view of surrounding hillsides as a machine gunner 
was easily recognizable although the terrain is green and forested 
now 
i dug many foxholes in korea said byers whose family lives 
in woodbridge va this one was special i didnt think id 
survive it 
he has 42 years in the army and is scheduled to retire next year 
from the 2nd infantry division the outfit he started with and 
rejoined last year 
ive made a complete circle korea and back to korea an 
