<TEXT>
aeroflots resumption of service to 
indonesia in july is another sign of improving relations between 
the soviet union and southeast asia which were sour throughout the 
1980s 
flights between moscow and jakarta were halted in 1982 after two 
soviet diplomats and the head of the soviet airlines jakarta 
office were accused of spying and expelled 
malaysia had ousted three soviet diplomats for the same reason 
in 1981 singapore expelled a soviet diplomat and a shipyard 
technician in 1982 accusing both of espionage 
soviet warships and planes occupied former us bases in vietnam 
and military aid from moscow sustained vietnams occupation of 
cambodia 
the red army was fighting in afghanistan and posted along the 
border with china relations between the kremlin and japan were 
strained because the soviets still hold the kurile islands 
captured late in world war ii 
suspicions remained even after president mikhail s gorbachev 
promised in a speech at vladivostok in july 1986 that the soviet 
union would mend its ways in the region 
mochtar kusumaatmadja then indonesias foreign minister 
expressed the general attitude with this comment it is a good 
beginning but there is a long way to go 
old perceptions of the soviet union have been swept away by 
recent events however and abu hassan omar the current foreign 
minister announced a new policy in may 
he told the international affairs forum in kuala lumpur that 
gorbachevs reforms had changed moscows presence in the region 
from offensive to one of no particular threat 
some in southeast asia have been encouraged by the soviet 
withdrawal from afghanistan and its participation in diplomatic 
efforts to resolve the cambodian conflict particularly welcome was 
the promise of reduced soviet military presence in vietnam 
the soviets are already in the process of unilaterally drawing 
down their offensive capabilities in danang and cam ranh bay abu 
hassan said my assessment is that the soviet union will now be 
more inward looking and will require a peaceful and stable 
international environment to pursue reform and economic development 
at home 
earlier this month gorbachev and president roh taewoo of south 
korea met in san francisco 
diplomats said attitudes in the region began changing 
dramatically last year when gorbachev did not intervene to stop 
communist regimes from falling in eastern europe 
the soviet unions political image has improved dramatically 
but its quest for greater trade and investment has been less 
successful 
japan and the united states dominate commerce in the pacific 
basin the soviets also must overcome perceptions that they produce 
shoddy goods and pay slowly 
moscows application to join the united states japan canada 
australia new zealand and the european community as a dialogue 
partner with the association of southeast asian nations was 
rejected last year 
asean links brunei indonesia malaysia the philippines 
singapore and thailand to promote regional economic cooperation 
officials of the organization said the soviet union was told to 
apply again later when its economic presence in the region was 
stronger a soviet request to take part in the new and larger 
asiapacific economic cooperation forum brought the same response 
we look forward to the soviet union participating in the rapid 
growth of this region said prime minister lee kuan yew of 
singapore a stalwart anticommunist 
within asean western diplomats say the soviet union seeks the 
closest ties with president suhartos administration in indonesia 
also rigorously anticommunist 
indonesia has 178 million people and offers a large relatively 
unexploited market 
thirty years ago the late soviet leader nikita khrushchev also 
saw indonesia not vietnam as the key to the region 
suharto made what jakarta regards as a highly successful visit 
to moscow in september since then indonesian ports have been 
reopened to soviet shipping and restrictions have been eased on the 
entry of soviet citizens 
in january president mirza olim i ibragimov of the soviet 
republic of uzbekistan became the highest soviet official to visit 
in 25 years 
</TEXT>
