standing about 20 feet tall on a platform in 
the louisiana superdome was a huge replica of an open bible 
the book was the cynosure of last weeks convention of southern 
baptists who perpetuated a leadership that insists on a singularly 
defined view of the contents 
avowing that view is the new criterion for job security among 
the thousands of staff members missionaries executives and 
professors of the nations largest protestant denomination 
the requirements elaborate details beyond any of the classic 
christian creeds specifying that acceptable belief for 
denominational personnel must include these spelledout 
affirmations 
that the worlds creation occurred as the bible recounts it 
that adam and eve were real individuals that all the biblically 
related miracles happened literally as described that moses wrote 
the first five books of the bible that all biblical narratives are 
historically flawless 
its the equivalent of a creed said the rev john lee 
taylor a gainesville ga pastor and of an expanded kind 
baptists historically have shunned creeds proclaiming no 
creed but the bible and emphasizing the soul competence of 
individuals to interpret scripture as they understand it but the 
new yardstick enjoins precise judgments 
its another example of the exclusivism being established in a 
denomination that historically has been open to diversity taylor 
added 
the new prescriptions were approved by a 1987 convention 
dominated by a fundamentalist majority that has wielded influence 
since 1979 and which this time increased its hegemony winning the 
powerful presidency for the 12th successive year 
that bloc rose to power over the 149millionmember 
denomination on the basis of politicalstyle organization and 
campaigning under the banner of biblical inerrancy and rightist 
social positions 
inerrancy is a relatively new term in christian annals 
meaning that the bible is totally free of error about science 
history geography biology religion and all other fields 
considering the typical baptist devotion to the bible any talk 
of threats to it is bound to set off alarm bells and that 
evidently is what happened from fundamentalist charges that 
denominational offices were infested with liberals downgrading 
the bible 
the canonading directed at seminary professors and various 
