the decadelong battle getting only 42 percent of the vote 
but that still represents a lot of baptists in a denomination of 
nearly 15 million and what theyll do remained uncertain under the 
tightened demands for conformity and the fundamentalist sweep 
some moderates foresaw an erosion of support to national 
denominational operations and increased links to alternative 
groups such as the baptist alliance set up to resist 
fundamentalist ascendancy 
in any case for the present the multibilliondollar 
