primarily in automobiles 
once an auto industry insider bourke is critical of us 
carmakers for being slow to develop engines that use lightweight 
aluminum parts but he said the loss of cheap and plentiful 
gasoline along with competition from abroad have been generating 
big scale orders from detroit 
