the recapitalization another move that points away from a breakup 
of the company 
analysts see rjr nabisco returning to public ownership 
beginning at some point in the next few years that is the route 
taken by another kohlberg kravis holding safeway stores inc 
after safeway went private in a 1986 leveraged buyout the 
supermarket company began hammering away at its debt and 
streamlined its operations this past february 3 years after the 
buyout the company announced a modest initial offering of 10 
million shares 
rjr nabisco said it was negotiating new loans with banks as part 
of the recapitalization plan the company said it expected to begin 
enacting the plan by the end of july 
the recapitalization is intended to take off the market some of 
rjr nabiscos junk bonds that have declined in value during recent 
months a buyback of the bonds would allow kohlberg kravis to 
sidestep provisions requiring the firm to guarantee the price of 
the bonds by next april 
the plan is likely to lower the return for kohlberg kravis and 
its investors but without a recapitalization rjr nabisco would 
end up paying a higher interest rate on the bonds 
rjr nabisco bonds rose sharply wednesday on word of the 
recapitalization gaining as much as 625 per 100 in face value 
kohlberg kravis investors mostly are large pension funds that 
generally do not have an active voice in the management of the 
companies they own including rjr nabisco officials of several 
funds declined to comment on what theyd like to see happen to rjr 
nabisco 
but several said they were satisfied with the management of 
their investments 
david weig executive director of the washington state 
investment board said he was absolutely happy with the 
management at rjr nabisco and with kohlberg kravis 
oregon state pension officials also said they were happy we 
have had excellent returns from these kinds of investments said 
sheryl wilson executive director of the states retirement funds 
