<TEXT>
pathe communications corp 
continues to negotiate financing for its 12 billion offer for 
mgmua communications co but seems unlikely to complete the deal 
by a saturday deadline 
mgmua officials were discussing extending the deadline for the 
20ashare tender offer spokesman scott tagliarino said 
wednesday he noted that pathe so far has fulfilled its obligations 
to mgmua including delivering 200 million in down payments 
pathe headed by italian financier giancarlo parretti has 
extended its offer several times past its original close date of 
april 30 
saturday is the latest possible deadline under the agreement 
between parretti and mgmuas controlling shareholder kirk 
kerkorian further extensions would require an allnew agreement 
tagliarino said 
pathes problems are with its chief backer time warner inc 
which has agreed to loan pathe 650 million of the purchase price 
time warner has insisted that the remaining 600 million must 
not come from borrowed funds and that pathe put up 450 million of 
that equity itself 
so far parrettis proposed patchwork of loans through european 
affiliates of pathe has failed to meet time warners criteria 
attorneys for both companies continued to negotiate wednesday 
even pathes 200 million in down payments were made with 
borrowed funds time warner spokeswoman marilyn harris said 
the 200 million is not equity its a loan ms harris said 
according to its agreement with pathe mgmua could pocket the 
200 million if the deal falls apart in return for issuing 10 
million new shares of common stock to parretti pathe also has 
guaranteed mgmua 75 million in fees for distributing pathe films 
in exchange for providing financing time warner would get a 
lien on the united artists movie library distribution rights to 
that library and distribution rights to future pathe and mgmua 
releases 
pathe spokesman craig parsons said discussions with time warner 
include whether the 200 million down payment is equity an even 
bigger issue is a proposed 368 million loan from parrettis 
luxembourgbased holding company comfinance sa which in turn 
was to raise the money from a variety of asset sales and borrowings 
pathe plans to repay comfinance in shares of stock thereby 
converting the loan to equity parsons said 
time warner also is concerned whether the loans and asset sales 
to finance the comfinance loan will materialize as billed 
for example in a security and exchange commission filing last 
week pathe said an affiliate would sell a 27 percent stake in a 
milan bank for 525 million to centro nord commissionaria a 
financial company however the financial times a british 
newspaper quoted centro nords president as saying no such deal 
had been agreed upon 
